<HEADLINE> Mongolia Gets Soft Loan From ADB </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
has agreed to grant a 15-million-dollar soft loan to Mongolia,
said M. Bold, vice-president of MongolBank on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The money will be lent for 30 years with an interest rate of 0.
75 percent.
</P>
<P>
Bold said some of the money will be used in the financial
sector to help create a stable financial environment with a
healthy banking system to stimulate economic growth. The rest will
be transferred to the state coffers to pay for salary and pensions
as well as investment.
</P>
<P>
The loan will be implemented in the next three years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
