<HEADLINE> Danish Beer Giant Carlsberg Merges With Orkla </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The Danish beer giant Carlsberg
and Norway's Orkla Wednesday announced a merger to create the
world's fifth largest beer brewing company -- Carlsberg Breweries,
it is reported here.
</P>
<P>
The new company would have annual sales of 25 billion Swedish
kroner (2.8 billion U.S. dollars). The company, which is to be
headquartered in the Danish capital of Copenhagen, will employ 27,
000 people.
</P>
<P>
Beer brewing will make up of 90 percent of the new company's
production. 
</P>
</TEXT>
