<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Syria Demands Israel Withdraw From Shebaa Farms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Syrian Foreign Minister Faruk
Shareh said Israel should withdraw from Shebaa Farms in accordance
with the U.N. Security Council Resolution 242.
</P>
<P>
After his meeting with U.N. Special Envoy to the Middle East
Terje Roed Larsen here on Wednesday, Shareh told the Arab Syrian
News Agency that Larsen raised the issue of Shebaa Farms, saying
the disputed area does not belong to the authority of the U.N.
Interim Force in Lebanon (UNITIL).
</P>
<P>
"Rather, the area belongs to the authority of the U.N.
Disengagement Observer Force (UNDOF) on the occupied Syrian Golan
Heights," Shareh quoted Larsen as saying.
</P>
<P>
"We made it clear to him (Larsen) our position on the necessity
of Israel's withdrawal from Shebaa Farms. The area should return to
Lebanon or Israel should withdraw therefrom in compliance with the
U.N. Security Council Resolution 242 that demands Israel to
withdraw from the Golan Heights without delay," Shareh added.
</P>
<P>
"There could be no dispute between Syria and Lebanon on
sovereignty over the Shebaa Farms," he asserted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
