Peter Robinson denied that his party's rotation plan was designed
to disrupt the executive.
</P>
<P>
He said that although the DUP would rotate ministers, its
policies would remain the same.
</P>
<P>
Among the other issues discussed at Thursday's three-hour
meeting was the flying of the Union flag over government buildings.
</P>
<P>
Ministers put off any decision, agreeing to "monitor the
situation and try to get an agreement". 
