<HEADLINE> Cuba Reacted with Caution after Legal Verdict on Boy Elian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, June 1 (Xinhua) --Cuban authorities reacted Thursday
with caution following U.S. Court of Appeals of Atlanta
announcement refusing right of political asylum to boy Elian
Gonzalez.
</P>
<P>
An official item disclosed by all Cuban media said it isn't
clear if the boy will be able to go back right away to Cuba, or on
the contrary will be retained in United States for an indefinite
time.
</P>
<P>
The text notified that distant relatives of the boy's lawyers
and anti-Cuban groups backing them have announced they are ready
to appeal..
</P>
<P>
Currently, the Gonzalez family are living in a Rosedale
residence, Washington, from where they hope to return to their
island after the Atlanta Court verdict regarding political
asylum resources put in by distant relatives.
</P>
<P>
Elian Gonzalez isn't entitled to an asylum hearing, a court
ruled Thursday, in a victory for the Cuban boy's father, who wants
him to return to Cuba.
</P>
<P>
Under the Atlanta court's ruling, Elian must remain in the
United States for 14 days to give his Miami relatives a chance to
appeal.
</P>
<P>
U.S. President Bill Clinton was pleased with the ruling, saying
the father is best suited to speak for the Cuban boy. "This is a
case about the importance of family and the bond between a father
and son," Clinton said in a statement from Berlin, where he was on
a weeklong European tour.
</P>
<P>
The three-judge panel of the Atlanta court said the Immigration
and Naturalization Service's decision that only a parent can act
for his 6-year-old child in immigration matters "was within the
outside border of reasonable choices." It said that principle held
even if the parent was in another country and the child was in the
United States.
</P>
<P>
Lawyers for the relatives said Thursday that they have not
decided whether they will request a rehearing. Lawyer Kendall
Coffey called the decision "very painful," but he said the 11th
Circuit judges "have been very fair." 
</P>
</TEXT>
