<HEADLINE> Cambodia Will Strive to Catch Up with Other ASEAN Members: PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Cambodian Prime Minister
Hun Sen reaffirmed here Thursday that peace and political
stability has returned in Cambodia and his country will strive to
catch up with other ASEAN members and fulfill its commitment to
achieving ASEAN's 2020 vision and the Hanoi's Plan of Action.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the dinner hosted by Singapore Prime Minister Goh
Chok Tong in his honor, Hun Sen said that his government has
achieved many satisfactory results in many fields and "Cambodia
will actively participate on an equal footing in all ASEAN forum
to achieve the 2020's vision and the Hanoi's Plan of Action".
</P>
<P>
"To achieve this goal, Cambodia will make its best effort with
its partners within ASEAN and with the assistance from other
friendly countries to eliminate as soon as possible the gap
existing between the new and the old members of ASEAN," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Moreover, Cambodia is already committed to implement the AFTA'
s time frame as it had been fixed with the purpose of acceleration
of the ASEAN economic integration," he added, referring to the
implementation of the ASEAN Free Trade Area by 2010.
</P>
<P>
Goh Chok Tong said that with peace in Cambodia and a favorable
environment there is a real chance for Cambodia to rebuild itself
and integrate effectively into ASEAN, noting Cambodia has already
made concrete contributions to ASEAN's market integration despite
being ASEAN's newest member.
</P>
<P>
"I especially welcome your desire to speed up the reduction of
tariffs for Cambodia and to implement AFTA earlier than was
required for the newer ASEAN countries," Goh added.
</P>
<P>
On bilateral relations between Cambodia and Singapore, Hun Sen
said that "Singapore could play an important role to assist
Cambodia to achieve its socioeconomic development, especially in
human resources development which is a fundamental factor for real
economic progress".
</P>
<P>
He said economies of the two countries can be complementary
for the mutual benefit of each other, noting that Cambodia needs
modern technology in many fields and private investment from
Singapore but Cambodia also has its economic potential essential
for the economic cooperation between Cambodia and Singapore for
mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
Goh said the Singapore government encourages Singapore
businessmen to trade and invest in the region including Cambodia
and will continue to share its development experiences with
Cambodia through technical assistance programs, adding he also
encourages qualified Cambodian students to take advantage of the
many scholarships in Singapore that are available to ASEAN
students.
</P>
<P>
According to Goh, total bilateral trade between Cambodia and
Singapore in 1999 stood at more than 460 million U.S. dollars, up
32 percent over that in 1998 and Singapore's investment in
Cambodia has totaled more than 200 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen arrived here this morning for a three-day official
visit at the invitation of his Singapore counterpart Goh Chok Tong.
</P>
</TEXT>
