<HEADLINE> Hungary's GDP Grows Nearly 7 Percent in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Hungary's gross domestic product (
GDP) grew 6.8 percent in the first quarter of the year over the
same period last year, said the country's statistical bureau on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The first three months this year witnessed the greatest
quarterly jump of the GDP since the quarterly statistics began in
1995.
</P>
<P>
In the past three years, Hungary's economy has enjoyed a steady
growth, with the GDP growth rate above 4.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The bureau attributed the growth in the first quarter mainly to
increases of investment, industrial production, and exports.
</P>
<P>
However, some experts believe that part of the reason for this
year's high growth rate in the first quarter is because growth in
the same period last year was slow.
</P>
<P>
They estimate that growth will slow down in the following
quarter. 
</P>
