<HEADLINE> Italian Garzelli Wins 18th Stage at Tour of Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Stefano Garzelli of Italy won the 18th
stage of the Touor of Italy cycling race on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to provisional results, Garzelli is the first rider
to cross the finish line of the 173-kilometer stage from Genoa to
Pratonevoso.
</P>
<P>
Gilberto Simoni and Francesco Casagrande, all from Italy,
finished second and third respectively and CAsagrande retained the
overall lead. 
</P>
