<HEADLINE> Militants Fire Rockets in Jammu, Kashmir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An official spokesman said that militants fired three rockets
at a security camp at Khundroo in Achabal area of Anantnag
district in South Kashmir Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to the Press Trust of India, two rockets fell short
of the camp and another did not explode. Nobody was hurt in the
explosions caused by bursting of rockets and the subsequent firing.
</P>
<P>
A soldier was killed and two others injured in a powerful blast
inside the Headquarters of Jammu and Kashmir Light Infantry.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, security forces shot dead 11 militants in separate
encounters in Jammu and Kashmir. 
</P>
</TEXT>
