<HEADLINE> Prices of Silver, Gold Down in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ready silver (.999 fineness) dropped sharply by 20 rupees (0.46
U.S. dollars) to 7,830 rupees (182.10 dollars) per kilogram from 7,
850 rupees (182.56 dollars) Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Raw silver (.916 fineness) was also quoted lower at 7,700
rupees (179.07 dollars) per kilogram as compared to 7,750 rupees (
180.23 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, standard gold eased by 10 rupees (0.23 dollar) to
close at 4,365 rupees (101.51 dollars) per 10 grams from 4,375
rupees (101.74 dollars) previously.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-two-carat gold also edged down by 5 rupees (0.12 dollar)
to close at 4,040 rupees (93.95 dollars) per 10 grams from 4,045
rupees (94.07 dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
