<HEADLINE> Senior Chinese Military Officer Visits Portugal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, June 1 (Xinhua) -- General Zhang Wannian, vice chairman
of China's Central Military Commission, arrived here Thursday
morning for a four-day official visit.
</P>
<P>
In a written statement distributed to the press upon his
arrival at the airport, Zhang said his visit is aimed at promoting
cooperation between the military forces of China and Portugal in
various fields, thus contributing to the development of the
overall relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said that since the establishment of diplomatic ties
between the two countries in 1979, friendly cooperation in
political, economic, cultural, military, and scientific and
technological fields has witnessed great progress.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government and the People's Liberation Army attach
great importance to cooperation between the two countries and the
military forces, Zhang said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
