<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rural Bank Gets More Loan Quota </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The move is designed to encourage the Rural Credit Union to
give more loans to farmers.
</P>
<P>
By the end of April, the Rural Credit Union had a total savings
deposits of 1.373 trillion yuan, accounting for 12.11 percent of
the country's total. By the end of April, it also gave loans of
985.56 billion yuan, accounting for 10.2 percent of the country's
total.
</P>
<P>
Both the amount of savings deposits and loans at the Rural
Credit Union have grown remarkably since the beginning of the year.
Among the loans, 337.123 billion yuan were given to farmers,
increasing 34.428 billion yuan since the beginning of the year.
</P>
<P>
According to People's Bank of China, some 92.5 percent of the
newly increased loans to farmers in the first quarter over the
year were from the Rural Credit Union.  
</P>
</TEXT>
