<HEADLINE> Chinese Young Pioneers Holds Fourth National Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BEIJING, June 1 (Xinhua) -- A total of 600 Chinese Young
Pioneers (CYP) deputies from all over the country gathered here to
celebrate the International Children's Day and attend the Fourth
National Congress of the CYP this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The Party and State Leaders Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, Zhu Rongji,
Li Ruihuan, Hu Jintao, Wei Jianxing and Li Lanqing met the
deputies and warmly greeted all children from around the country.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice President Hu Jintao said that all Chinese
youngsters will grow up together with the rapid development of
their motherland, while a promising new century is approaching.
</P>
<P>
They are expected to be strict with themselves, to be good
students at school, good children at home and good children in
society. They must strive to become talented young adults, said
Hu, who is also a member of the Standing Committee of the CPC
Central Committee Political Bureau.
</P>
<P>
He said that the CYP is a cradle for nurturing China's
children and provides a school where children can learn socialism
and communism.
</P>
<P>
The young pioneers deputies also announced the "China's Youth
Declaration in the 21st Century" at the conference. 
</P>
