<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Zhou Li, a member of the former
Central Advisory Commission of the Communist Party of China (CPC),
passed away at the age of 97 on May 22.
</P>
<P>
Zhou used to be the secretary of the CPC Committee of Hunan
Province in central China and chairman of the provincial committee
of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC).
</P>
<P>
Chinese leaders Li Peng, Zhu Rongji and Hu Jintao and other
senior officials have expressed their condolence to Zhou's family.
