<HEADLINE> Taliban Lodge Protest over Air Space Violations by  Uzbekistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Afghanistan's ruling Taliban
militia Thursday formally lodged protest with Uzbekistan over
claimed air space violations by Uzbek planes.
</P>
<P>
Taliban's representative to Pakistan Maulvi Syed Mohammad
Haqqani told a group of Islamabad-based journalists that
Uzbekistan's fighter planes violated Afghan air space on May 30
and May 31.
</P>
<P>
Haqqani said that a protest note was handed over to the Uzbek
Embassy in Islamabad, urging the Central Asian republic to halt
violations of Afghan air space.
</P>
<P>
According to the Taliban diplomat, Uzbek planes entered into
Afghan air space up to one kilometers twice on May 30 and again on
May 31. He did not specify the areas where the violations occurred.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban militia control most of the Afghan territory except
some areas in northeastern part of the country while Uzbekistan
lies north of Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Haqqani said the Taliban has also complained to the United
Nations of violations of Afghan air space by Uzbek planes.
</P>
</TEXT>
