<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Mika Hakkinen set the fastest time in
free practice for Sunday's Monaco Grand Prix on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Hakkinen drove his McLaren-Mercedes through Monte Carlo's tight
street corners to clock a leading time of one minute 21.387
seconds for his fastest lap, beating German Michael Schumacher to
the second place at 1:21.486.
</P>
