<HEADLINE> China, Kazakhstan Combat Locust </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region in
northwest China signed an agreement this week with neighboring
Kazakhstan to combat plagues of locusts.
</P>
<P>
Locust rampages have destroyed two million ha. of crops in
bordering areas between Xinjiang and Kazakhstan this summer.
</P>
<P>
The two sides agreed to take coordinated action to wipe out the
locusts. 
