<HEADLINE> Joint Business of East China's Civil Aviation Taking Effect </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 1 (Xinhua) -- China Eastern Airlines and
Shanghai Airlines, two major airlines in east China, have
significantly increased their profits since April 1 when they took
part in a joint program launched by the General Administration of
Civil Aviation of China (CAAC).
</P>
<P>
Officials from the Eastern China Branch of CAAC today also
revealed that the sector safely carried 2.51 million people in
April, up 19.2 percent on an annual basis, with the number of
passengers increasing by eight percent.
</P>
<P>
The program involves a total of 108 domestic air routes.
</P>
<P>
Insiders noted that the program has led to positive competition
among airlines, as well as effectively improving transport
capabilities and stabilizing prices. 
</P>
</TEXT>
