<DOCNO> XIE20000601.0096 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HKSFC Chairman Stresses on Disclosure of Info </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Disclosure of information is of
critical significance for today's economy under the combined
impact of globalization, technology and innovation, according to
Andrew Sheng, chairman of the Hong Kong Securities and Futures
Commission Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"Reliable, accurate and timely information is a market
fundamental," Sheng said at the Organization for Economic
Cooperation and Development (OECD)'s Second Asian Roundtable on
Corporate Governance, which was opened here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The market needs high quality information, timely disclosures
and efficient access to such information to maintain integrity and
to function fairly and efficiently, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Asian financial crisis has demonstrated that Asia has gaps
in disclosure, incentives to use information, the law and
regulatory net and capacity to use information, he said.
</P>
<P>
He also pointed out that raw information is useless without
high quality accounts, including non-financial information,
prepared according to international accounting standards and
verified or audited according to international or generally
accepted auditing standards.
</P>
<P>
"Participation in the global economy imposes obligations as
well as providing opportunities. To exploit fully the benefits of
greater and cheaper sources of investment provided by
international capital, corporations must accept the disciplines of
better financial disclosure and high quality audits," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000601.0097 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Middle East Economic Briefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The following are economic briefs from
the Middle East countries.
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- Governor of the Central Bank of Lebanon Riad Salame
announced on Thursday that the total remittances sent home by
Lebanese expatriates is estimated at 3 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Salame said the exchange rate between U.S. dollar and Lebanese
pound has recently witnessed a decline, which is a good sign after
the Israeli pullout from south Lebanon last Wednesday. He expected
that the country's economy will develop faster with the prevailing
political stability.
</P>
<P>
Salame said the deposit periods for Arab funds in the bank,
including 500 million dollars from Saudi Arabia and 100 million
dollars from Kuwait, will be extended next year.
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- The Turkish government decided on Wednesday to
gradually limit the currently unlimited state guarantee for bank
accounts, reported Anatolia News Agency on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
It also decided that non-guaranteed deposits at the collapsed
offshore banks will be compensated by the state.
</P>
<P>
However, state compensations to deposit holders at the collapsed

offshore banks will not cover all deposits, and only deposits up to
20 billion Turkish Liras (about 3,000 U.S. dollars) would be
compensated.
</P>
<P>
The move is reported to be part of the banking reforms requested
by the World Bank.
</P>
<P>
SANAA -- Syria has achieved an average 5.5 percent of growth in
gross domestic product (GDP) over the past five years and its per
capita income now averages at 1,243 U.S. dollars, said Syrian
Minister of Economy and Foreign Trade Mohammed al-Imady, currently
on a visit to Yemen.
</P>
<P>
He said during the five-year period, the agricultural sector
scored a growth rate of 5.8 percent, the industrial sector of 7.7
percent, construction of 7.6 percent and finance, insurance and
real estate sectors of 9.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
The exports volume in 1999 reached 4.4 billion dollars while
imports volume stood at 6 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Damascus is now considering joining the World Trade Organization
(WTO), the minister added.
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Turkey is constructing a giant viaduct in Nurdagi
township of Gaziantep Province, bordering Syria, within the
framework of Tarsus-Adana-Gaziantep (TAG) Motorway, reported
Anatolia News Agency on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
An official with Turkey's Highways General Directorate told
reporters on Thursday that the viaduct, named "Ataturk Viaduct,"
is 146-meter high and 801.50-meter long.
</P>
<P>
The viaducts and tunnels, which are located in the quake-prone
zone, is being constructed with special methods, which will be able
to resist earthquakes measuring 8.0 degrees on the open-ended
Richter scale.
</P>
<P>
The official, however, added that the tunnels are not built on
the
active fault lines and that there is not a massive quake risk in
the area.
</P>
<P>
RIYADH -- A Saudi company, specialized in melting, casting and
designing jewelry and gold, is working on designing the world's
largest ring.
</P>
<P>
The ring, weighing 57 kilograms in net, is made of 21 karat pure
gold and is of 2.5 meters in diameter.
</P>
<P>
An official of the Tiba Jewelry and Gold Company said that the
ring will be put on show in the Western Zone of the kingdom and
other places for a month. The company intends to record the ring in
the Guinness Book of Records, said the official.
</P>
<P>
The ring, which will be manufactured by dozens of designers and
highly sophisticated machines, will be embellished with 25,000
karat of precious stones.
</P>
<P>
The company is planning to showcase the ring in shopping
festivals to be staged in Saudi Arabia, Dubai Emirate of the United
Arab Emirates, Egypt and other international fairs this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
