<HEADLINE> Kim Jong Il Returns to Pyongyang After Visit to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Leader of the Democratic People's
Republic of Korea (DPRK), Kim Jong Il, returned here Thursday
morning after a visit to China from May 29 to 31, the Korean
Central News Agency (KCNA) reported.
</P>
<P>
Kim, who was invited by Jiang Zemin, Chinese president and
general secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party
of China, had a warm meeting and held talks with Jiang, the state
news agency said.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Kim also met Li Peng, chairman of the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress, Premier Zhu
Rongji, and Li Ruihuan, chairman of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference.
</P>
<P>
At the talks and meetings, achievements and experience in
socialist construction of the two parties and two countries were
introduced and an unshakable will was manifested to further
consolidate and develop the traditional DPRK-China friendship,
said the KCNA report.
</P>
<P>
Kim also visited Tian'anmen, the main gate to the Forbidden
City, and a computer plant of the Legend group. 
</P>
