<HEADLINE> Bomb Explosion on London Bridge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 1 (Xinhua) -- A road bridge in west London was hit
by an explosion early Thursday, but no casualties or injuries were
caused, police said.
</P>
<P>
A high-explosive device attached to a girder under the south
side of Hammersmith Bridge went off at 4.30 a.m. (0330 GMT) and
the bridge was slightly damaged.
</P>
<P>
Anti-terrorist officers were investigating a possible link with
Irish dissident groups.
</P>
<P>
A police spokesman said no warning was given and no one had
claimed responsibility for the explosion.
</P>
<P>
Police closed the bridge and one of the main commuter routes
into the British capital, severely disrupting traffic.
</P>
<P>
Northern Ireland's Ulster Unionist deputy leader John Taylor
said he believed that dissident republicans intent on
destabilizing the peace process may have been responsible.
</P>
<P>
Later on Thursday, the Northern Ireland Assembly will meet for
the first time since power was restored to the province. Sinn Fein
and unionist members will sit together in the power-sharing
executive. 
</P>
</TEXT>
