<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Champion Li Pulls out But Still Qualifies for Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Liu Hongyu and Wang Yan, who
finished 1-2 in the women's 20km walk event at the World
Championships in Seville last year, walked just a few kilometers
before pulling out of the Chinese national championships and
Olympic trials here on Thursday, but they still qualify for the
Sydney Olympics.
</P>
<P>
"Liu and Wang had automatically made the Olympic squad because
of their fabulous performance at last year's World Chammpionships,
" said Shang Xiutang, general secretary of the Chinese Athletic
Association (CAA).
</P>
<P>
The event was won by their training partner Wang Liping, who
clocked a personal best time of one hour 28 minutes 33 seconds.
Sun Chunfang finished second in 1:29:45 while Tang Yinghua came
third in 1:30:36.
</P>
<P>
With Wang Liping joining Liu and Wang Yan to compete in Sydney,
Shang believes that the women's 20km event will be the best gold
hope for China's track and field in the coming Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
"Even compared with coach Ma Junren's long distance runners,
the three athletes have a better chance to win an Olympic gold
medal," Shang said.
</P>
<P>
China claimed one athletics gold medal each from the last two
Olympic Games through Chen Yueling from the women's 20km walk at
Barcelona in 1992 and Wang Junxia from women's 5,000m at Atlanta
in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Liu Hongyu and Wang Yan just returned from their package warm-
up tournaments in Europe and their coach Zhang Fuxin said they
should spend a period time recovering from fatigue.
</P>
<P>
"Liu won three races in Portugal, England and Germany while
Wang won the champion in Spain, " Zhang said. "They should take a
rest, so I let them drop out today."
</P>
<P>
Zhang said their biggest threat came from Russia, who had four
people clocked inside one hour 25 minute in the Russian Olympic
Trials early last month.
</P>
<P>
"That's really unbelievable. But that will not impose pressure
on our athletes. We still have time and we have the confidence to
beat them in Sydney."
</P>
<P>
In the men's 20km event, former World Cup champion Li Zewen won
the title in 1:23:09, followed by Bai Liansheng in 1:23:34 and He
Xiaodong in 1:23:45. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000601.0104 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Regulating Grain Purchasing Prices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The State Development Planning
Commission(SDPC) said today that it will strengthen regulation
over grain purchasing prices in China's provinces and regions.
</P>
<P>
The SDPC stressed the consistent prices in different regions,
which it held fundamental to China's reform in the grain
circulation system.
</P>
<P>
The local government should consult grain purchasing prices in
neighboring provinces before deciding its own pricing policy.
Those who violate the price agreement will be punishment,
according to new rules set by the SDPC.
</P>
<P>
The new rule will help local governments to control grain
purchasing as well as facilitate reform in the grain circulation
system, SDPC said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
