<HEADLINE> Beijing Implements Water-Saving Measures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Beijing Municipal Government will
adopt effective measures to save limited water resources, said
Mayor Liu Qi at a water conservancy meeting held here today.
</P>
<P>
Liu said that that water from lakes and rivers will be used to
irrigate 1.3-million-square-meters of urban greenbelts instead of
tap water. Beijing will reduce 70,000-mu rice plantation areas in
order to conserve 2.8 million cubic meters of water.
</P>
<P>
A metropolis with a population of 12 million people, Beijing
does not have sufficient water resources. Three hundred cubic
meters of water is used per capita, one eighth of the country's
average water resources.
</P>
<P>
Liu stressed that the water-saving program is also important
for Beijing's bid for the 2008 Olympic Games. 
