<HEADLINE> Energy Development Urgent for Asian-pacific Region:  ESCAP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The UN Economic and Social Commission for Asia and the Pacific(
ESCAP) points out in a report that the task of energy development
in the region's developing countries, which have a widening gap
between energy demand and supply, is particularly pressing.
</P>
<P>
To push forward energy development, it suggest that
implementing minimum energy efficiency product standards could
play a positive role.
</P>
<P>
Increasing usage of enviroment-friendly fuels such as natural
gas and renewable sources of energy would be another good choice,
it said.
</P>
<P>
Continued increase in energy demand in the region also poses a
big challenge in providing affordable and sustainable energy
service, and the possible options may include fuel switching,
demand-side management and energy conservation, it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
