<DOCNO> XIE20000601.0153 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rainfall to Alleviate Drought in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Heavy rains and showers are
expected to alleviate the sustained drought in the Huaihe and
Hanshui river valleys early this month, according to the Central
Meteorological Observatory.
</P>
<P>
Rainfall ranging from 10 to 30 millimeters is forecast for the
Sichuan Basin, southern parts of Shaanxi and Hubei provinces,
central and southern parts of Henan Province, central and southern
parts of Shandong, Jiangsu, and Anhui provinces, northern part of
Hunan Province, central and northern parts of Jiangxi and Zhejiang
provinces, eastern part of the Yunnan-Guizhou Plateau, and western
part of south China.
</P>
<P>
The rainfall may be as much 80 to 120 mm in a few isolated
areas, the source said, adding that northern part of Xinjiang,
eastern part of northwest China, and southern part of north China
will also see rain in the next few days.
</P>
<P>
The rainfall, with occasional rainstorms and strong winds, will
possibly influence the harvesting of summer crops.
</P>
<P>
North China has been suffering from a severe drought due to
little rainfall and high temperature since early spring.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000601.0154 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Ensures Telecom Inter-Network Connections (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 1 (Xinhua) -- China is taking measures to ensure
telecom inter-network connections, according to a high ranking
official with the Ministry of Information Industry.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Chunjiang, vice-minister of the Information Industry,
said that a new regulation on telecom management, which will take
effect in the near future, will clearly define inter-network
connections as the basic responsibility of telecom operators.
</P>
<P>
It also rules out the arbitrating procedure when cutting a
telecom inter-network, said Zhang in an interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
"There will be no real competition without an unlocked inter-
network connection," said Zhang.
</P>
<P>
With China's market continuing to open, keen competition has
emerged in the telecom sector. But what the Chinese government
wants is "orderly and cooperative competition," Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Information Industry recently dealt with a case
of cutting an inter-network connection because of competition in
Fuyang City in east China's Anhui Province. One manager of a
local company was fired as a result.
</P>
<P>
Zhang noted that most of the cases of cutting inter-network
connections occurred because of the interweaving of government
functions with the management of local telecom administrations. (
more)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
