<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India Sees 30.77 Pct Export Growth in April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to the monthly trade data released Thursday by the
Ministry of Commerce. the country's exports recorded 3.4 billion
U.S. dollars in the first month of the 2000-2001 fiscal year as
against a mere 2.6 billion dollars in April 1999.
</P>
<P>
Imports during April 2000 is valued at 4.5 billion dollars
representing a growth of 43.64 percent over the 3.15 million
dollars worth of imports in April 1999.
</P>
<P>
Trade deficit in April 2000 was put at 1.1 billion dollars
which is more than double the 523 million dollars trade deficit in
April 1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
