<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Asia's Small Business Facing Challenge: UN Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The report, issued by the UN Economic and Social Commission for
Asia and Pacific(ESCAP), pointed out that these businesses are
still dependent on outdated, labor intensive technology, and rely
heavily on low labor costs.
</P>
<P>
To increase the role of Asian small and medium-sized businesses
in the global market, it suggested that information technology is
especially needed.
</P>
<P>
A recent study conducted by the ESCAP found that certain
conditions are needed for diffusing information technology into
these businesses,such as establishing a legal framework for e-
commerce, increasing access to relevant information, building
business awareness and improving the information infrastructure,
it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
