<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Montenegrin President's Security Adviser Murdered </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, June 1 (Xinhua) -- A close adviser of Montenegrin
President Milo Djukanovic was shot dead late Wednesday,
registering the fourth assassination against senior Yugoslav
officials this year, the Montenegrin Television reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Goran Zugic, 45, security adviser of Djukanovic, was murdered
in front of his home in Podgorica, capital of the small Montenegro
republic, which forms Yugoslavia with Serbia.
</P>
<P>
One of Zugic's neighbors said he heard the shooting and found
Zugic lying dead near his car.
</P>
<P>
After the accident, police blocked all main roads of Podgorica
to look for the murderer.
</P>
<P>
Several senior Yugoslav officials were killed in mysterious
shootings this year, including Pavle Bulatovich, the country's
defense minister, who was killed at a restaurant in Belgrade in
February. 
</P>
</TEXT>
