<HEADLINE> Indian Airlines Resumes Flights to Kathmandu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After the resumption of flights, IC-813/814 will fly Delhi-
Kathmandu-Delhi daily, while IC 747/748 will fly Calcutta-
Kathmandu-Calcutta five times a week -- except on Thursday and
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
According to Civil Aviation Authority Nepal, the Kathmandu-
Varanasi flights will be resumed soon, though the exact date has
not been fixed.Varanasi is a holy city in northern India.
</P>
<P>
The Indian Airlines suspended all its flights to Kathmandu
after the hijacking of its passenger plane en route from Kathmandu
to Delhi on December 24 last year.
</P>
<P>
The two countries had bickered over the safety measures at
Kathmandu international airport with India insisting on deploying
its own security personnel at the airport.
</P>
<P>
Several rounds of talks between civil aviation authorities of
the two countries led to the resolution of the dispute, though no
details relating to the agreement were disclosed. 
</P>
