<HEADLINE> Zambia to Host Paris Club Consultative Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Zambia will for the first time in
history host Paris Club's Consultative Group (CG) meeting next
month, Times of Zambia newspaper reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
It quoted Chileshe Kandeta, a public relations official with
the Ministry of Finance, as saying the objectives of the Lusaka CG
meeting will be to review Zambia's economic reform program,
particularly the assessment of the interim poverty reduction
strategy paper, sectoral programs and public sector reform.
</P>
<P>
Also under review will be the Zambian government's medium term
economic strategy and good governance efforts.
</P>
<P>
This is in order to reach a decision on financing of the gap or
 shortfall in resource requirements for financing the country's
economic plan with donor in-flows, Kandeta said.
</P>
<P>
The four day intensive meeting will be between Zambia and all
its cooperating partners drawn from among the Paris Club members
and multilateral institutions and will run from July 16 to 19 at
the request of finance minister Katele Kalumba. 
</P>
