<HEADLINE> Share Prices Rise Sharply in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices rose sharply in Tokyo
Thursday, led by high-priced information and technology stocks,
with the benchmark Nikkei index closing above 16,600 for the first
time in nine trading days.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange climbed 361.85 points, or 2.22
percent, from Wednesday's close to end at 16,694.30.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, advanced 19.14 points, or 1.26 percent, to 1,
541.98.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section increased to 654.43 million
shares from Wednesday's 609.52 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Akai Electric was the day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
Several leading information and technology issues drew active
buying, traders said, adding that rubber, retail and real estate
issues also saw large gains.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, losers included paper manufacturers, steelmakers and
electric power and gas firms, as well as construction firms.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, gainers outnumbered
losers 720 to 504, with 173 issues closing unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
