<HEADLINE> Computer Contest Marks Children's Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Many thousands of Chinese children
observed International Children Day today in their own special way
-- participating in a nationwide computer contest.
</P>
<P>
The opening ceremony of the contest was held this morning at
the Great Hall of the People, where Li Tieying, a member of the
Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party
of China, kicked off the contest by pressing a computer key.
</P>
<P>
The 11th International Children's Day Computer Contest is
jointly sponsored by 11 government departments, including the
Ministry of Information Industry and the Ministry of Health.
</P>
<P>
For the occasion, China Telecom for the first time issued a
special Internet card for Chinese children aged three to 18 years
old so that more children would be able to participate in the
contest.
</P>
<P>
By using the card, the children can surf the Internet at a cost
of only 1.5 yuan per hour, compared with the standard four yuan
per hour.
</P>
<P>
The contest is expected to last for about seven months.
