<HEADLINE> Indian IT, Software Exports up 35 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to the Electronics and Computer Software Export
Promotion Council (ESC), the IT sector contributed 15 percent of
the total export earnings during the last fiscal year against 12.4
percent in 1998-1999 with 177.75 billion rupees (4.13 billion
dollars).
</P>
<P>
India exported 173 billion rupees (4.02 billion dollars) worth
of computer software and services last fiscal against 125 billion
rupees (2.91 billion dollars) in 1998-1999, registering a growth
of over 38 percent in rupee terms.
</P>
<P>
Electronics hardware sector recorded a 27 percent growth last
fiscal with exports earnings of 26 billion rupees (60.47 million
dollars) against 20.50 billion rupees (47.67 million dollars) in
1998-1999. 
