<HEADLINE> Ukraine Claims to Be Strategic Non-nuclear Power </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine has "necessary abilities and
means" to be a strategic non-nuclear power and it will form rapid
reaction forces in five years, said Ukraine Defense Minister
Alexander Kuzmuk.
</P>
<P>
Kuzmuk made the announcement Wednesday when introducing a five-
year plan on military development, which was passed Tuesday by a
national security and defense meeting, reported the Interfax News
Agency.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine, whose strategic non-nuclear armaments include missiles
and heavy bombers, is making efforts to establish comprehensive
missile equipment in order to further achieve military
modernization, said Kuzmuk.
</P>
<P>
Under the five-year plan, Ukraine will size down its military
personnel from 310,000 to 295,000 by 2005 and reduce non-military
staff in the army from 90,000 to 80,000 at the same time, aiming
to form a professional army, added Kuzmuk. 
</P>
