<HEADLINE> 16 Killed, 50 Injured in Tanker Blast in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 1 (Xinhua) -- At least 16 people were burnt to
death and 50 others injured, 15 of whom seriously, as an oil
tanker caught fire Wednesday in Chittagong, the second largest
city in Bangladesh, The Independent newspaper reported here
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
It is the worst accident in the long history of ship breaking
that started here in 1976.
</P>
<P>
According to police and witnesses, the explosion occurred when
some 150 workers engaging in breaking the 53,300 metric ton oil
tanker at the Shitalpur ship breaking yard were cutting and
breaking it with the help of gas.
</P>
<P>
Immediately the oil tanker caught fire which instantly engulfed
it. Ten of the victims died on the spot, and the injured were sent
to nearby hospital immediately.
</P>
<P>
Police sources said the search for trapped workers inside the
huge ship was still on and the casualty figure may rise.
</P>
<P>
Bangladeshi Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina on Wednesday night
expressed deep shock at the death of the victims in the gas
explosion.
</P>
<P>
In a message of condolence, she expressed her sympathy to the
members of the bereaved families and prayed for the peace of
departed souls. She also prayed for early recovery of the injured
people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
