<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kala-azar Kills 27 People in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-seven people have died of
Kala-azar during the past one month in villages of Udaypur
district in eastern Nepal, and the death toll is still rising,
according to a report reaching here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The report said one or two people are dying almost everyday in
the affected area and the epidemic has not yet been put under
control.
</P>
<P>
The report said a special team of doctors sent from Kathmandu
established a medical camp in the affected area Wednesday to treat
patients and curb the spread of the epidemic.
</P>
<P>
Kala-azar, virulent infectious malarial disease of oriental
tropics, is one of the common diseases in Nepal that takes a toll
of at least several hundred people every year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
