<HEADLINE> India Defeats Bangladesh in Asia Cup Cricket </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Indians warmed up well for today's
crucial match against Asia Cup champions Sri Lanka, crushing
Bangladesh by eight wickets Wednesday in the seventh Asia Cup
Cricket at the Bangabandhu National Stadium, The Independent
newspaper reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
However, the second encounter of the Asia Cup was not
embarrassingly one-sided as the result suggested and the home side
piled up what looked like a challenging total.
</P>
<P>
"We batted too well in the start and had a huge total by the
25th over. It gave us the chance to bat with ease after that,"
said Indian captain Ganguly who pocketed 3,000 U.S. dollars for
all three prizes: man-of-the-match, the most-valuable player and
hitting most sixes.
</P>
<P>
Satisfied with his own performance, the Indian captain didn't
forget to praise his opponents, saying the overall team
performance of Bangladesh is improving.
</P>
<P>
Bangladeshi Captain Bulbul also admitted that the Indians
batted extraordinary, but he regarded Wednesday's show as
Bangladesh's best batting performance ever, hoping this match
would give them confidence to play better in the future. 
</P>
