<HEADLINE> Gunman Takes 23 Children and Three Adults Hostage in Luxembourg </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 1 (Xinhua) -- A gunman took 29 children and
three adults hostage at a daycare center in a small village in
eastern Luxembourg near the border with Germany late on Wednesday,
according to reports reaching here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The 39-year-old gunman came into the daycare center in the
village of Wasserbillig with a pistol, hand grenade and knife and
took the three workers and the children aged from several months
to eight years old, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Special operations police members armed with rifles have sealed
off the building and conducted a long night negotiation by
telephone with the gunman who is a Luxembourg citizen with
Algerian origin and has a history of mental illness, Interior
Minister Michel Wolter told a news conference.
</P>
<P>
The gunman demanded 60 million Belgian francs (1.5 million U.S.
dollars and a plane to fly him to Libya later on Thursday, he said.
</P>
<P>
"I have given the orders that the situation be ended without
violence, negotiations are still going on," said Wolter.
</P>
<P>
The children have had food and drinks, and medicines would be
taken into the building, he said.
</P>
<P>
The kidnapper first seized 49 children and adults at around 3:
30 p.m. (1330 GMT) Wednesday, and released 16 of his hostages a
few hours later, police officers said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
