<HEADLINE> Netherlands Women Beats Olympic Champion Australia in Field Hockey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The Netherlands women's team
defeated Olympic Champion Australia 2-1 on Wednesday in the
Champions Trophy field hockey tournament in Amsterdam, Netherlands,
avenging lossed in both the Olympic and World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
The Netherlands got penalty corner goals from Julia Deiters in
the 12th minute and Susan van der Wielen scored in the 49th minute.
Australia closed the gap in the 56th minute on a tally by Katrina
Powell.
</P>
<P>
This was only Australia's fourth defeat in Champions Trophy
play since the competition's inception in 1987.
</P>
<P>
Australia is now third in the six-nation league with one match
remaining. Germany led with 10 points, followed by Netherlands
with nine points and Australia with six.
</P>
<P>
In two other women's matches on the day, Germany tied New
Zealand 2-2 and Argentina drew with South Africa with an identical
score. 
</P>
