<HEADLINE> Sino-U.S. Cooperation on Green Textbook </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 1 (Xinhua) -- A cooperative project between
Chinese and U.S. environmentalists will soon bring a new textbook
into Chinese classrooms, China Daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
Early last year, the Global Environmental Alliance China began
translating into Chinese "E 2: Environment and Education", a
textbook used in the United States.
</P>
<P>
Ten thousand copies of the translation will be distributed to
pilot schools by the alliance, which was founded by the Ministry
of Science and Technology and U.S. Global Communications for
Conservation.
</P>
<P>
The textbooks promote innovative teaching methods and exchange
between teachers and students.
</P>
<P>
They are being used in 55 primary and secondary schools in
Beijing, reaching 7,000 students.
</P>
<P>
Schools in other cities will use the textbooks soon, said Laura
Utley, chairman of the Global Communications for Conservation.
</P>
