<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, May 31 (Xinhua) -- NATO will start two-week large-scale
air force maneuvers next Monday in northern Europe, a spokesman
for the Command in Allied Air Forces Central Europe announced
Wednesday in a NATO air base in western Germany.
</P>
<P>
Thirteen of the 19 NATO countries, including the two new
members of Poland and the Czech Republic, will send air forces to
join the exercises, Lieut. Col. Walter Schneider said in the
command's headquarters, Ramstein Air Base.
</P>
<P>
During the maneuvers, NATO fighters will fly over 10 NATO
countries -- Germany, France, the Netherlands, Belgium, Luxembourg,
Denmark, Britain, Norway, Poland and the Czech Republic.
</P>
