</P>
<P>
DAMASCUS -- Syria has fully accepted Israel's withdrawal from
south Lebanon, without demanding Israel pull out from the disputed
Shebaa Farms, said U.N. special envoy to the Middle East Terje
Roed-Larsen here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Larsen said in a statement that Syria and the United Nations
agreed "on every matter" related to the pullout, which was hastily
completed last Wednesday. (Syria-Israel-Withdrawal)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- The Lebanese parliament held a historic special
session Wednesday noon in Bint Jbeil town in south Lebanon to
commemorate the "martyrs" who died in Lebanon's 22-year struggle
against Israeli occupation, Oriental radio reported.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time that the Lebanese parliament met in south
Lebanon since 1978 when Israel invaded Lebanon and occupied part
of its southern territory. (Lebanon-Parliament-South)
