<HEADLINE> Corinthians Edges Palmeiras 4-3 with Last-minute Goal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Corinthians defeated
Palmeiras 4-3 with a last minute goal in a thrilling first leg of
the Libertadores Cup semi-finals on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Ricardinho put Corinthians ahead in the 15th minute following a
clever pass from Edu.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian champions continued to dominate but a mistake by
Marcelinho in the 39th minute saw Junior level the scores.
</P>
<P>
Palmeiras showed their good team work before the break but were
stunned in the 45th minute when Marcelinho's shot was diverted
into his own goal by Palmeiras defender Argel for Corinthians to
go in 2-1 up at half time.
</P>
<P>
Edilson made it 3-1 in the 65th minute. But Palmeiras hit back.
In the 75th minute Alex headed a Junior cross and Euler equalised
the score in the 79th.
</P>
<P>
In a frantic finale Corinthians wrested the victory when
Vampeta's deflected long-range effort flew into the top corner.
</P>
<P>
The second leg match is on June 6. 
</P>
