<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Maternal Care Centers for Rural Women </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Care centers for women in
central China's Henan Province are the first place that local
women turn to when they need contraceptives, or when they want to
confide in someone.
</P>
<P>
"When these care centers were first set up they only provide
contraceptives for bearing-age women, but now they also provide a
range of other services related to sex," said Xue Lixia, who runs
the center.
</P>
<P>
A woman surnamed Han in Xiaohancun called Xue, worried that she
is not interested in sex. She slept badly since her mother passed
away, and she disliked her husband touching her.
</P>
<P>
Xue told her it was not a major problem, but her depression has
affected desire to have sex. It would be better for Han to express
her concerns and share her feelings with her husband.
</P>
<P>
Xue said her center has helped 47 couples resolve their marital
problems due to problems in their sex life.
</P>
<P>
More care and individual services will ensure that family
planning policy will be smoothly carried out, said Wang Xianzhi,
demographer in the province.
</P>
<P>
Cui Xiaoling, a 29-year-old married woman in Caipocun Village,
told Xue that she could not get pregnant in the first five years
of marriage. She dared not tell anyone else, fearing ridicule and
gossip from others. Xue suggested that she undergo an examination.
Cui got pregnant soon after a salpinx operation.
</P>
<P>
The family planning policy implemented in China in the 1970s
only provided two contraceptive choices: ligation operations or
contraceptive ring insertions. Rural females can readily get
contraceptives from the center with information on how to use them.
</P>
<P>
"Incidences of gynecological diseases has dropped thanks to the
centers," said Chen Ruoli, vice-head of the provincial family
planning commission.
</P>
<P>
In the past, women were not allowed to bathe one month after
they gave birth, which was supposed to be bad for their health.
Procreation health publicity activities inform rural women how to
take care of themselves.
</P>
<P>
The province, the most populous one in China with a population
of 93 million, started women care service for bearing-age women in
1996. There services include medical examinations every two months
for all women and birth consultation services. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
