<HEADLINE> Website for Kids Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The website, www.chinachildren.net.cn, was jointly launched by
the Ministry of Culture, China Society for Promotion of Culture
and Arts for Children, and Zhongtong Information Network Co., Ltd.
in Shanghai, to mark the 16th anniversary of Deng Xiaoping's call
to popularize computer knowledge among children, People Daily
reported.
</P>
<P>
The website, opened on May 28, came as a special gift for
Chinese children for their holiday -- the June 1 International
Children's Day.
</P>
<P>
China currently has over 10 million Internet users and more and
more children are getting online.  
</P>
