<HEADLINE> Danish Team Invited on Tour de France for First Time </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Kelme of Spain, Denmark's Memorycard,
invited for the first time, and French outfit Bonjour were given
the three Tour de France team wild cards on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The three teams were added to the 17 automatic qualifiers when
Tour director Jean-Marie Leblanc announced the line-up for the
world's leading endurance race which begins at Futuroscope on July
1.
</P>
<P>
Kelme were selected as their leader Fernando Escartin finished
third last year, taking the Spanish entry to three teams including
Banesto and ONCE.
</P>
<P>
Bonjour were preferred to the other two French candidates, Jean
Delatour and Bigmat-Auber, following their victory in the Midi
Libre. It will be the first Tour de France since 1996 without
Bigmat.
</P>
<P>
Memorycard won this year's Dunkirk Four Days and their rider Bo
Hamburger a stage of the Paris-Nice race. 
</P>
</TEXT>
