<HEADLINE> Russia Ties Slovakia 1-1 in Soccer Friendly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 31 (Xinhua) -- A second half header by Vladimir
Beschastnykh gave Russia a 1-1 draw against Slovakia in a friendly
soccer match on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Marek Uilucky put the Slovakian team ahead after 25 minutes
when his second attempt beat Alexander Filimonov from close range.
</P>
<P>
Beschastnykh, a Spain's Racing Santander stiker, re-directed an
Andrei Tikhonov's cross in the 60th minute to save the Russians an
embarassing defeat to the Slovaks.
</P>
<P>
Neither side qualified for the European Championships which
began on June 10 in Brussels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
