<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Plaza Takes Lead in Tour of Germany Cycling Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Spaniard David Plaza moved to the
head of the field in the Tour of Germany Cycling Race after
winning the seventh stage on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Plaza completed 35.7-kilometer seventh stage with a time of 42
minutes 53 seconds, 40 seconds clear of his rivals in the town of
Herzogenaurach.
</P>
<P>
Plaza totalled 27 hours 52 minutes 57 seconds in overall
standings.
</P>
<P>
Germany's Andreas Kloeden and Udo Boelts finished second and
third place in the overall standings after finishing second and
fifth respectively.
</P>
<P>
The Tour ends on Thursday in Berlin. 
