<HEADLINE> Conference for Children and Peace Opens in Athens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ATHENS, June 1 (Xinhua) -- A two-day conference for children
and peace opened here Thursday with the aim of helping create a
civilization of peace through the twin axes of family and
education.
</P>
<P>
The Athens-Delphi International Meeting for Children and Peace
has been organized by the Foundation for Children and Family under
the auspices of the United Nations Educational, Scientific and
Cultural Organization (UNESCO) and in cooperation with the
International Peace Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the conference, UNESCO Goodwill Ambassador Marianna
Vardinoyianni said that people should teach children to declare
war on wars, which were responsible for killing 1.5 million
children,maiming 4 million children, uprooting 20 million children
and the 13 million children now living in destroyed cities.
</P>
<P>
She stressed that children were those most deeply affected by
wars.
</P>
<P>
The conference is part of a UNESCO program for a "civilization
of peace" aimed to coincide with the declaration by the U.N. of
the year 2000 as the International Year for Peaceful Civilization
and Non-Violence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
