<HEADLINE> Argentina Seizes One Ton of Marihuana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Argentine authorities seized
one ton of marihuana in Misiones province from a cargo bus
traveling southward.
</P>
<P>
According to police sources of the province, the drug was
concealed beneath a load of dovetailed wood carried by a truck
that had arrived in Misiones a few days ago, coming from
Gualegauychu, Entre Rios province.
</P>
<P>
The operation was carried out proceeding from confidential
reports predicting entry to the country, from Paraguay, of an
important marihuana load, along Parana river.
</P>
<P>
Police warned that traffickers' activity is greater after May
and until July of every year. 
