<HEADLINE> Eight Peasants Murdered in Colombia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Eight Colombian peasants have been
shot by alleged members of the paramilitary group, the United
Autodefenses of Colombia (AUC) in two acts carried out in
different points of the country, authorities said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
AUC members of the county's main paramilitary organization
murdered Wednesday night five peasants in a small country house in
Sucre department, northeast of the country.
</P>
<P>
Paramilitary men took the farmhands out of their homes in
Libertad village near San Onofre municipality (Sucre), and shot
them down.
</P>
<P>
Identities of these mortal victims haven't been provided, an
official police source in Sincelejo, capital of Sucre, said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In another similar act, carried out also by the AUC, three
peasants were shot in the small village of Las Minas de Iraca,
Cesar department, north of the country, according to police
sources. 
</P>
