<HEADLINE> Europe's Major Stocks Make Strong Gains </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Europe's major stock markets all
posted strong gains Thursday as investors turned again to telecom
and technology stocks.
</P>
<P>
London's benchmark FTSE 100 index advanced 111.2 points, or 1.
75 percent, to close at 6470.50 as media and telecom components
surged in late session.
</P>
<P>
With cable firm Telewest Communications topped the index with a
11.7 percent advance while Internet security firm Baltimore
Technologies ended 10.3 percent higher after having been down 2
percent.
</P>
<P>
Telecom and media shares that had languished in morning trade
rebounded later in the session, telecom equipment manufacturer
Marconi climbed 6 percent and satellite TV operator BSKyB rose 8.6
percent.
</P>
<P>
The pan-European FTSE Eurotop 300 rose 1.21 percent to close at
1614.70, with media and tech sub-indexes posting the strongest
gains, while food and chemicals shares lost ground.
</P>
<P>
German shares outperformed Europe in extremely thin turnover,
however, Frankfurt's Xetra Dax closed up 163.09 points, or 2.29
percent, at 7272.76, with broad-based gains.
</P>
<P>
The CAC 40 in Paris closed up 173.45 points at a record 6599.
71 having earlier nosed above 6000 as investors piled into its
heavyweight telecom and media shares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
