<HEADLINE> Panama Urges Colombia to Help Free Abducted Man </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Panama's Foreign Ministry urged
Thursday Colombia's government to help free a Panamanian citizen
kidnapped on Colombian territory by a guerrilla group.
</P>
<P>
Through an appointment with Colombia's ambassador in Panama,
Ramon Martinez, the foreign ministry stressed that Colombia's
government must assume responsibility for kidnapping case of
Panamanian citizen Nicolas Alberto Perez.
</P>
<P>
The Foreign Ministry expressed belief that Colombia's
authorities will bring into force mechanisms to which Colombia's
government has access for contributing a peaceful resolution to
this lamentable case.
</P>
<P>
The Panamanian was kidnapped on April 12, 1999, by National
Liberation Army (ELN) with 65 passengers who traveled Aboard a
commercial flight of Avianca airline.
</P>
<P>
Up to date, all those kidnapped have been freed, excepting
this Panamanian citizen and five other Colombians. 
</P>
</TEXT>
