<HEADLINE> Panama, US Sign Investment Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to the protocol, at any moment after six months
following the date on which the difference comes forth on
Panamanian land, Panamanian or American investors can submit it
to conciliation or obliged arbitrage to international instances.
</P>
<P>
Panama's Foreign Minister Jose Miguel Aleman said after signing
the document that this protocol assures investors there is greater
fluidity in any existent claim and that they feel there are
guarantees.
</P>
<P>
He noted that this protocol, which will enter into force from
its signing, carries with it a purpose of trying to speed up
foreign investment in Panama.
</P>
